{
  "stem": "11472.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He left as long-- he left, and he said to me, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Take care of your mother and your sister, Simala.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I kept that vow to my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I kept that promise.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was-- I'm a devoted sister.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We love each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She's devoted to me, too.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We love each other so, my sister and I.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't know if there are any other sisters that love each other that much.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We speak to each other-- she lives in Montreal, Canada-- every day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We're on the phone to each other.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My mother was sick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She had cancer.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I took care of my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The doctors used to say, you're like a, a watch dog.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We've never seen anyone-- I knew-- I loved my mother, of course.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I knew that it was my responsibility.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father, he was such a nice man.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Anyway, I started to go to school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My grandfather started to, started to do business.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And you know, whenever you're a little girl, you go to school with other children, with Polish children, Ukrainian children.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "My mother opened up a little store.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They, they allowed her to have a little store since her husband was in the army and she had no way of supporting herself.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So she was allowed to sell, like, shoelaces and yeast and-- not big things, you know, but just to make a, a mere living for herself and her children.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "My grandfather started to-- they took over our house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "My grandfather started to deal, you know, wheel again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They bought right away a horse and wagon or they took back a horse and wagon from the, from, from the peasants, whatever.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Borszczow.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is in the summer.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
